The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Mohun Bagan and top three teams from Singapore (Tampines Rover), Malaysia (Pehang) and Thailand (Ostopa M-150 FC) will vie for top honours in the Group E of the AFC Cup to be held from March 6-May 22.

 Having qualified for the prestigious tournament after emerging champions in the Federation Cup recently, Mohun Bagan will face a challenge from Tampines Rover at the Salt lake Stadium from 6 pm. 

 Mohun Bagans new coach Chima Okerie feels that the international meet will give an opportunity for their players to compete against the best of the teams, especially when the NFL is on. 

 An unbeaten 122 by Bengal opener Arindam Das helped Sporting Union beat Netaji Subhas Institute by seven wickets in a CAB First Division league match on Thursday. 

 FOOTBALL: National League: Mohun Bagan vs Mohammedan Sporting (Barasat Stadium 2.30 pm)

 CRICKET: The Telegraph six-a-side Merchants Cup at CC amp;FC from 5 pm.




